                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(right)\">\n                <placeName>Binghamton</placeName>\n                <date>June 21<hi rend=\"sup\">st</hi> 1860</date>\n            </p>\n            <p><addressee>Revd. Isaac Leeser</addressee>,</p>\n            <p>Dear friend,</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(2)\">As the Advertise-<lb/>ment in the Occident inserted<lb/> for my\n                benefit has effected<lb/> naught in all this time; it appears<lb/> to me useless to\n                continue it longer.<lb/> Permit me again to thank you<lb/> for having inserted it.\n                    <del>and</del> Please<lb/> inform me of the amt of my<lb/> indebtedness. Should\n                you at any<lb/> time hear of any family residing in<lb/> a healthy, pleasant,\n                location where<lb/> I might find a desirable home,<lb/> I shall be greatly obliged\n                to you,<lb/> to apprise me of it. I think<lb/> at any rate of remaining here\n                this<lb/> summer as I would not like<lb/> to <sic>undergoe</sic> the fatigue of<lb/>\n                packing &amp; traveling during the<lb/> warm season. I have the plea-<lb/>sure of\n                having my sister <persName>Julia</persName>,</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3t72824r/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
